article.headline: W. Illinois 28, N. Dakota St. 16
article.story: FARGO, N.D. -- Caulton Ray rushed for 106 yards and a touchdown and Matt Barr threw two TD passes to Lito Senatus as Western Illinois defeated North Dakota State 28-16 Saturday. Bryce Flowers added 82 rushing yards and a score for the Leathernecks (4-1, 2-0 Missouri Valley), who won their third straight. Brock Jensen passed for 239 yards and scored on a 1-yard run for the Bison (3-2, 0-2). Ryan Jastram kicked three field goals. Barr connected with Senatus for a 6-yard TD pass in the first quarter for the game's first points and found him again with a 1-yard scoring pass in the third for a 28-13 lead. Ray and Flowers both scored in the second quarter, and Western Illinois took a 21-6 lead into halftime.
